# HarmonyOS ArkTS And ArkUI Coding Standards

## Purpose

Use this rule before generating or editing ArkTS, ArkUI pages, abilities, extension abilities, or app utilities.

## ArkTS Syntax Guardrails

Do not generate these patterns in ArkTS code:

- CommonJS `require()`
- object spread such as `{ ...obj }`
- array spread such as `[ ...items ]`
- `delete target.key`
- `eval()`
- dynamic property names or bracket-based object mutation when a typed property is expected

Use these replacements:

- ES module imports such as `import fs from '@ohos.file.fs'`
- explicit object construction with named fields
- `items.slice()` when a shallow array copy is needed
- assign `undefined` or rebuild a typed object instead of using `delete`
- typed switch/if mappings instead of runtime evaluation
- declared interfaces/classes instead of dynamic dictionaries when possible

## File System API Rules

- Do not use `fs.readTextSync` or `fs.writeTextSync`.
- For text files, use `fs.openSync` with `readSync` or `writeSync`, then convert bytes with `util.TextDecoder` or `util.TextEncoder`.
- Always close file handles in cleanup paths.
- Keep blocking file I/O out of UI render paths and gesture callbacks unless the data volume is known to be tiny and the task explicitly accepts the tradeoff.

## Naming Conventions

- Page files: PascalCase, for example `Index.ets` or `SettingsPage.ets`.
- Utility files: camelCase when the file exports utility functions, or PascalCase when it exports a main class.
- Components and structs: PascalCase.
- Functions and methods: camelCase.
- Constants: use the nearest existing app convention; prefer clear typed constants over magic literals.

## Import Conventions

- Prefer default module imports such as `import fs from '@ohos.file.fs'`.
- Avoid `import * as X from '@ohos.module'` unless an existing local file already uses that form for the same module and ArkTS accepts it in this workspace.
- Keep imports static and top-level.
- Do not reference modules that are not available in the current HarmonyOS SDK or app dependency set.

## State Management

- Use `@State` for local mutable UI state owned by the component.
- Use `@Prop` for one-way data received from a parent.
- Use `@Link` only when a child must mutate parent-owned state.
- Do not use global mutable state as a shortcut for page coordination when a typed property, route parameter, service, or app metadata can carry the data.

## Gesture Conventions

- Use `.gesture(LongPressGesture().onAction(...))` for long press interactions.
- Do not use `onLongClick`; it is not the preferred ArkUI pattern in this workspace.
- Keep gesture callbacks short. Move non-trivial work into named methods or services.
